Sister/Twinning cities[edit]

Chattanooga has six sister cities, as designated by Sister Cities International: [223]
 Hamm, Germany (since 1975) [224]
 Wuxi, China (since 1982) [225]
 Giv'atayim, Israel (since 1988) [226]
 Nizhny Tagil, Russia (since 1996) [227]
 Gangneung, South Korea (since 2003) [228]
 Wolfsburg, Germany (since 2011) [229]
Chattanooga also has two twinning cities:
 Swindon, United Kingdom (since 2006) [230]
 Ascoli Piceno, Italy (since 2006) [231]
In January 2007, all of the cities above, with the exception of Wolfsburg, had a tree native to each locale planted at Coolidge Park's Peace Grove, which was established to replace a 100 year-old Slippery Elm tree which was damaged in a lightning storm in August 2006.[232][233] Wolfsburg was added in September 2011.[234] The Peace Grove has eight trees: a Linden Tree, which represents Hamm, a Chinese Elm, which represents Wuxi, a Mediterranean Cedar, which represents Giv'atayim, a White Birch, which represents Nizhny Tagil, a Ginkgo Tree, which represents Gangneung, an English Elm, which represents Swindon, a European Hornbeam, which represents Ascoli Piceno, and an Oak Tree, which represents Wolfsburg.
